meanings.definition: A habitational surname from a place in County Clare, Ireland.
meanings.english_definition: A surname of Irish origin, derived from a place name.

meanings.definition: A village in the administrative district of Gmina Łubianka, within Toruń County, Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-central Poland.

etymology.value: Irish: habitational name from a place in County Clare, named Banna, from beann ‘peak’, ‘gable’.
